<font color="#FF0000">UNDERSTANDING??</font><br>
<tt>Tue Dec 23 14:05:45 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was an MP in the 18th Bde.<br>
 well after TET. Not much going on around Tan Son Nhut. Mostly security stuff during the early 70's just before mass troop withdrawls. For several years after returning I felt I should have done more. For some reason I felt I owed more for what I was given, particularly to legs who spent time in combat. I didn't want to be them at the time, just felt at odds. I was 19.  When I got married in 1984, we needed to relocate. To finance the move, I did another enlistment. Went back through basic, AIT, etc., as a Cav Scout. I was surprised to find a number of namvets returning to service about the same time. The second enlistment didn't resolve a whole lot of issues in and of itself, as the Army, much like computer software has become much more user friendly.  Too much so. It wasn't the same in 1972.  However, the associations with other vets returning for whatever their reason, helped immensely. Those years were filled with a turmoil  I've yet to completely resolve and rarely discuss which has created some stress and difficulty in my marriage. I appreciate just being able to bring it out. <br>

